---
title: Chicken & Greek Salad Pita Pockets with Feta
description: This spin on classic Greek salad (no lettuce!) is full of flavor and texture contrasts to get your taste buds tingling. You’ll toss together juicy tomato, crunchy cucumber, scallion greens, and briny feta in tangy Greek vinaigrette. Load it all into warm pitas with garlicky sautéed chicken, and you’ve got a wholesome Mediterranean meal in minutes!

image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66fc21fe99e8e2a18bd71ec2-cd14149a.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66fda6a5966ea033d562cd6b-en-US.pdf
cuisine: Mediterranean
nutrition:
  calories: 800 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 45 g
  sugar: 4 g
  protein: 74 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1310 mg
course: main course
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-and-greek-salad-pita-pockets-66fda6a5966ea033d562cd6b
time required: 20 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Quarter @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1⁄4-inch-thick quarter-moons. Dice @tomato{1} into 1⁄4-inch pieces.

Open package of @chopped chicken breast{20%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and scallion whites in a single layer; season with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, tomato, scallion greens, @feta cheese{½%cup}, and @Greek vinaigrette{1.5%ounce}.

Wrap @pita bread{2} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Halve pitas; gently pull apart to create pockets.

Fill pita pockets with chicken and as much Greek salad as you like.

Divide pita pockets between plates and serve with any remaining Greek salad on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.